alfe-backend-autocad — AutoCAD driver (Windows COM, accoreconsole)
==================================================================

Status: closed
Landed in: ee45a36 "autolisp-front-end: land Phase 3 — BricsCAD +
AutoCAD backends." See autolisp-front-end/source/backend-autocad.lisp
and tests/backend-cad-tests.lisp.

Deferred items moved to other tickets:
  - EPURE gating (section 4) — moved to alfe-plugin-model.issue
    (no plugin model exists yet; the --epure flag parses but no
    backend acts on it, the VBS template does not yet activate
    the Epure profile).
  - vlisp-compile routing — confirmed out of scope per the issue's
    "Out of scope" note; the flag is accepted in argv and routed
    through to the engine, but alfe does not validate it.
  - Real-CAD smoke tests — gated behind AUTOCAD_SMOKE=1; the
    mocked-engine end-to-end test covers the protocol path.



See also: alfe.plan, alfe-backend-interface.issue,
alfe-file-protocol.issue, spec section "Backend autocad".

Context
-------

AutoCAD is Windows-only and offers two execution paths:

  - the full GUI via the `AutoCAD.Application` COM ProgID (required
    for `vlisp-compile` and any DCL/Visual-LISP feature), and
  - the headless `accoreconsole.exe` Core Console (faster, no GUI,
    but no `vlisp-compile`).

Both paths drive the AutoLISP REPL via the file-IPC protocol from
`alfe-file-protocol.issue`.

In scope
--------

  1. Platform gating. On macOS / Linux, `alfe --autocad` exits with
     code 3 and a structured "AutoCAD not distributed for this OS"
     message. No discovery attempted.

  2. Binary discovery (`alfe.backend.autocad:detect`):
       - `$AUTOCAD_EXE` → `/c/Program Files/Autodesk/AutoCAD\ */acad.exe`
         (descending) → `/c/Program Files/Autodesk/AutoCAD\ LT\ */acadlt.exe`
         (descending) ;
       - `$AUTOCAD_ACCORECONSOLE` →
         `/c/Program Files/Autodesk/*/accoreconsole.exe` ;
       - the detector returns *which* binary is available so the
         backend chooses between automation and batch.

  3. Automation mode (`alfe.backend.autocad.automation`):
       - Emit `bridge-autocad.vbs` matching the spec verbatim,
         including: `WaitQuiescent` polling on `app.GetAcadState`,
         explicit `Documents.Add` when no `ActiveDocument`, EPURE
         profile activation, `_SCRIPT` invocation for EPURE setup,
         `app.Quit` gated on `created And statusReadyFlag`, the
         `ATTACHED=`/`CREATED=` stdout protocol.
       - Map `AUTOCAD_COM_MODE` (auto/attach/launch/off) to the
         VBScript inputs.
       - Path-escaping helper (`Replace(..., "\", "/")` inside VBS
         for `(load …)` arguments).
       - VBScript debug log gated by `AUTOLISP_DEBUG` writing to
         `WORKDIR/debug.log` with `[VBS]` lines.
       - Status-wait policy: do NOT call `app.Quit` if the runtime
         hasn't published its final status — `kill_autocad_com_process`
         (legacy) becomes a CL-side helper that uses `taskkill /PID`
         on Windows.

  3. Batch mode (`alfe.backend.autocad.batch`):
       - Selected by `--mode batch` or `AUTOCAD_COM_MODE=off`.
       - Requires a DWG (`--dwg` / `$AUTOLISP_DWG`) and a `.scr`
         (the LSP transformed to a script).
       - Command:
            "<acc>" /i "<dwg>" /s "<SCRFILE>"
       - `vlisp-compile` errors out cleanly under batch mode with a
         documented diagnostic.

  4. EPURE gating. `--epure` under `--autocad` requires
     `AUTOCAD_EXE` (the full GUI binary); accoreconsole is excluded
     (no profile support). The profile activation
     (`app.Preferences.Profiles.ActiveProfile = "Epure"`) and the
     `_SCRIPT` invocation are wired in the VBScript template.

  5. VBS quoting helper. Implement the `escape_vbs_string` helper
     from the spec (double internal quotes; do not touch
     backslashes). Tests cover edge cases (embedded quotes, mixed
     slashes, UTF-8).

  6. Tests:
       - VBScript emission produces a file byte-identical to the
         documented template (modulo placeholder substitution),
         under each `AUTOCAD_COM_MODE` and with/without EPURE ;
       - parses ATTACHED/CREATED lines correctly ;
       - mocked-engine end-to-end via the file-protocol scaffold ;
       - real-AutoCAD smoke tests guarded by `AUTOCAD_SMOKE=1`.

Out of scope
------------

  - `vlisp-compile` reimplementation. Stays an
    `--autocad --mode automation` Windows-only feature; alfe just
    routes the call.
  - Pure-CL COM client (no VBS hop). A future ticket can move the
    bridge to `cffi` + `OAIDispatch`; for V1 keep VBScript.

Acceptance criteria
-------------------

  - `alfe --autocad` on macOS or Linux exits 3 with a clear
    "not distributed" message.
  - Emitted `bridge-autocad.vbs` matches the spec template
    byte-for-byte (after placeholder substitution); a fixture-based
    test enforces this.
  - `alfe --autocad --mode batch -l fixture.lsp` runs end-to-end
    under accoreconsole on Windows (opt-in test).
  - `alfe --autocad -x '(vlisp-compile (quote lsa)
    "src-vlx/schmsplus.prj")'` succeeds when run on a Windows host
    with AutoCAD installed.

Notes
-----

The AutoCAD VBScript bridge is the most fragile piece of the legacy
wrapper; the spec captures the hard-won robustness (`WaitQuiescent`,
status-conditional `Quit`, debug logging). Preserve every detail —
deviations show up as flaky CI months later. When in doubt, copy
the VBScript template verbatim into the CL emitter and parameterise
it only at the named placeholders.
